<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-03-22T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-03-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="256" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d256">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-03-22"><hi rend="italic">March 22,
                            1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>(Mr. Hay states, in regard to Articles VIII and IX of the joint note, that we
                        as signatories should, through our military representatives, join in
                        determining the measures as to which the right to subsequently participate
                        has been reserved by the United States.)</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>